urban: “For thousands of years, humans built cities by slowly, incrementally growing to reduce the risk of economic and social failure. endorsement: Former President Trump has said, “I will NOT be endorsing Terry Mitchell for Congress!”
inflation: The following questions will ask for your views on issues related to the economy and inflation. For reference, when the Bureau of Labor Statistics reported its August update at the end of the summer, the year-on-year inflation rate was 8.3% — above the previous decade’s yearly average — meaning that over the previous year, prices had risen by an average of 8.3%.
urban: “For thousands of years, humans built cities by slowly, incrementally growing to reduce the risk of economic and social failure. That all changed in the 1940s, when the federal government spent millions on highway and suburban expansion. Now, cities are economically insolvent, on average receiving 10 cents in revenue for every dollar spent on infrastructure and $5 trillion in infrastructure debt across the country.”
CampaignFocus1: Rural areas have not been fairly represented in the decision-making process at the national level. As a politician, I want to change that.
CampaignFocus2: As a politician, I want to focus more on my rural constituents by giving them the funding and attention they deserve to best represent their interests.
